This season we honor the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. by wearing his initials proudly across our chests. 22 Freedom Stars are featured on our historic Hawks MLK Nike City Edition Uniforms, representing the 22 times Dr. King was arrested fighting for justice and equality

We reflect on a pivotal moment in the civil rights movement with Dr. King’s arrest on April 12, 1963, when he famously penned his “Letter from a Birmingham Jail.” #EarnTheseLetters
